items.name: starlake
items.description:
此模型原本公开在抱脸上https://huggingface.co/PWB/starlake ，现5.0已完成，一并上传。

模型制作的初心是同时兼顾良好的背景和人物，但由于介于中间，既非画风特化也非风景特化导致地位较为尴尬，这也是一开始未在civitai上传的原因。

而后因为受到欢迎，遂上传之。

迭代5.0的过程也是几经波折...暂且按下不表。

5.0的不同点：

*软化了过拟合，现在不会倾向于自动加入过度的细节。

*tag服从度上升，需要写出对应元素才会出现。

*添加了金字塔噪声，现在可以直接画明暗差大的图。

This model was originally published on Hugging Face https://huggingface.co/PWB/starlake and is now completed in version 5.0 and uploaded together.

The original intention of the model making is to take care of both the background and the characters. The differences in 5.0 are:

  • Softened overfitting, now it will not tend to automatically add excessive details.

  • The tag obedience has increased, and corresponding elements need to be written to appear.

  • Added pyramid noise, now you can directly draw pictures with large differences in brightness.

你可以随意使用该模型，但请不要出售模型本身获利。注意吃相。

You are free to use the model, but please do not sell the model itself for profit.

items.name: Ramayana Style
items.description:
This model produces a style inspired by an ancient indian epic, the Rāmāyaṇa (or Ramayana). That and the Mahābhārata (or Mahabharata) are foundational ancient texts that form part of the Itihasa.

Using a weight of 0.5 to 0.8 appears to work best; less than 0.5 might work for your purposes too. Here's how to bring in this model at 0.7 weight in your prompt: <lora:ramastyle:0.7>.

I'm adding images generated with no additional Loras or negative prompts embeddings you would have to seek out, made with just the prompt, negative prompt, and base model. However, this model does seem to respond well to enhancers like Wowifier and more_details.

Ramastyle doesn't produce great hands or feet by itself.

It's my first uploaded model, and I'm not convinced it is great, but it often creates appropriate images that I enjoy. Comments and feedback greatly appreciated!

items.name: Gaunter O'Dimm | The Witcher 3 : Wild Hunt
items.description:
Character Lora of Gaunter O'Dimm from The Witcher 3 : Wild Hunt (Hearts of Stone).

"You wished to play? So let us play." -Gaunter O'Dimm

Expectation: G.o.D, Reality: S.o.B -soul3142


This work is licensed under a Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-NoDerivatives 4.0 International License.

If you want to, you can support me on Patreon or Buy me Coffee.

My Witcher LoRA Index - soul3142's Guide to the Witcher Universe. additionally you can check out some characters i've made from other games also.

Main Trigger Word - gaunterW3_soul3142 , check examples for other ones.

RECOMMENDATIONS :-

  1. Highres Fix - must, if you are getting blurry and ugly images

    My upscale method: txt2img 512x768 -> send to img2img -> controlnet tile upscale, tile diffusion 2x scale with 4xUltrasharp upscaler and tiled vae

  2. Weight: 0.6 - 0.8

  3. Clip Skip: 2

  4. Denoising - Don't go too high, it can alter a lot of details

  5. For better face's - you can use ADetailer

I use 0.7 weight, 25 steps, Euler a, Clip skip 2 in nearly all my examples with almost same, simple +ve/-ve prompts regardless of checkpoint for my own consistency purposes.

There are imperfections here & there, which i usually leave it in as is, (i never do any inpainting in examples), most of which like hands can be fixed with better prompting, negative embeddings while other like weapons are just bad majority of the time no matter the model as of today.

Some LoRA's are flexible with any clothing, some are not (usually character's with single costume) so keep these things in mind.

This is an unofficial fanmade LoRA, not intended for any commercial purpose and use. All characters and IP rights are owned by their respective creators and owners. I do not own rights to any of these characters.

items.name: Zendaya (JG)
items.description:
A commission I received through my website.

Zendaya Coleman is an American actress and singer, mainly known for her roles on films such as Dune or Spiderman: Homecoming and on some Disney Channel TV shows.

160-step TI trained on a dataset of 15 images with these settings.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

Since you're here, please also check @Bozack3000's fantastic version of Zendaya.

Building a good prompt with my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of extremely sexy (zend4y4:0.99), a woman as a sexy student, (closeup portrait), curly hair, ({white|yellow|pink|blue} tight long sleeve turtleneck top), at a cantina sitting bar (masterpiece:1.5) (photorealistic:1.1) (bokeh) (best quality) (detailed skin texture pores hairs:1.1) (intricate) (8k) (HDR) (wallpaper) (cinematic lighting) (sharp focus)"

Viggo Peter Mortensen Jr. R[2] (Danish: [ˈviko ˈmɒːtn̩sn̩]; born October 20, 1958)[3] is an American actor. He made his film debut in a small role in Peter Weir's 1985 thriller Witness. He appeared in several notable films, including The Indian Runner (1991), Carlito's Way (1993), Crimson Tide (1995), Daylight (1996), The Portrait of a Lady (1996), G.I. Jane (1997), A Perfect Murder (1998), A Walk on the Moon (1999), and 28 Days (2000).

Mortensen received international attention in the early 2000s for his role as Aragorn in the epic fantasy adventure trilogy The Lord of the Rings. In 2005, Mortensen won critical acclaim for his acting in David Cronenberg's crime thriller A History of Violence.[4] Two years later, Mortensen earned acclaim in another Cronenberg film, Eastern Promises (2007); he was nominated for the Academy Award for Best Actor. A third teaming with Cronenberg in A Dangerous Method (2011) resulted in a nomination for the Golden Globe Award for Best Supporting Actor – Motion Picture for his portrayal of pioneer psychiatrist Sigmund Freud. He gained additional Academy Award nominations for his leading roles in Captain Fantastic (2016) and Green Book (2018).

Aside from acting, Mortensen has explored fine arts, photography, poetry, and music. In 2002, he founded the Perceval Press to publish the works of little-known artists and authors.

items.name: Kafka (Honkai Star Rail)
items.description:
LoRA

A modular LoRA for Kafka from Honkai Star Rail. This LoRA allows for easy addition / removal of some characteristics of the character. Example below:

Example usage

Main tags:

  • Purple hair, purple eyes: for general face/eyes/hair

  • Black shorts: for the black shorts + purple straps

  • Purple pantyhose: for the purple pantyhose or purple thigh highs

  • Jacket, white shirt: for the white shirt + jacket (mostly shoulder jacket)

  • Purple gloves: for the purple gloves and some purple accents

I recommend using the fallowing propmt for general usage: KafkaHSR, purple hair, purple eyes, black shorts, purple pantyhose, jacket, white shirt.

I HIGHLY SUGGEST using an upscaler, I recommend the ESRGAN 4x+ for higher details and fixing any face/clothes issues.

All sample images are generated with my custom merged model UmbraMix

Prompts

  • Negative prompts should be as simple as possible such as (worst quality, low quality:1.4), (blurry:1.4).

  • All sample prompts are generated with a CLIP SKIP value of 2

  • When generating with the jacket keyword, I recommend using good negative embeddings to correct the morphology, it tends to generate multiple arms

Weights

I recommend using the fallowing weights:

  • aggressive: 0.8 ~ 0.9

  • soft / permissive: 0.35 ~ 0.55

VAE

I recommend using the kl-f8-anime2 VAE

items.name: Another Damn Art Model (ADAM)
items.description:
Another Damn Art Model (ADAM)

Questions/Feedback/Updates?

Visit my thread on the Unstable Diffusion Discord

Like Fantasy & Sci-fi Art? Check Out My New Model : Doomer Boomer

This merge is made up of different epochs and iterations of sample models I created to test a much larger fine tuned model I'm working on (Boomer art model).

Artist tags from the 1980s and 1990s Heavy Metal Magazine era can really improve the overall composition and style of the output generation.

List of Artists to Try :

  • Boris Vallejo

  • Julie Bell

  • Boris Vallejo and Julie Bell

  • Frank Frazetta

  • Luis Royo

  • Brom

  • Richard Corben

  • Larry Elmore

  • Olivia de Berardinis

  • Scott Hampton

  • Moebius

  • Milo Manara

  • Vince Gimenez (or just 'Gimenez')

  • Chris Foss

  • Philippe Druillet

  • Richard Cohen

  • Doug Chiang (Great for sci-fi landscapes)

  • H.R. Giger

  • Hajime Sorayama (or just 'Sorayama')

  • + more

Some artist tags will be more influential than others, this shouldn't be as much as a problem when the full model is released. Experiment with other artists not listed above, even some modern artists are known by the model. For example 'background by Jessica Rossier' can create some very beautiful sci-fi landscapes. If the artist style isn't pushing through enough, look down bellow and read "Neutral Prompt Hack".

Requirements

VAE Required: Download here

Install :

stable-diffusion-webui -> models -> VAE

In Webui :

Under Settings -> Stable Diffusion -> SD VAE select the downloaded VAE and uncheck Ignore selected VAE for stable diffusion checkpoints that have their own .vae.pt next to them

Settings

Clip Skip : 1

  • Settings -> Sampler parameters -> Clip skip

ETA Noise Seed Delta : 31337

  • Settings -> Sampler parameters -> Eta noise seed delta

Face Restoration : Disabled (See ADetailer)

  • IF enabled : Settings -> Face restoration -> CodeFormer -> weight = 0.8

Parameters :

  • Sampler :

    • I used a combination of Euler a, DPM++ SDE Karras for many of the sample images, but this is just personal preference.

  • Steps : Depends on the sampler, typically 20 - 35 works well.

    • If DDIM use higher steps

Hires Fix (Optional) :

  • Upscaler :

    • R-ESRGAN 4x+

      • Denoising strength : 0.3 - 0.35

      • Upscale by : 1.5 - 2 (can go lower but shouldn't go higher than 2)

    • Lolipop, 4x-UltraSharp, Remacri (foolhardy)

      • Can be downloaded here

      • Install to stable-diffusion-webui -> models -> ESRGAN

      • Typically Denoise ~= 0.5 - 0.6 (can go higher or lower)

      • Upscale by : 1.5 - 2

Extensions

ADetailer :

Extension for webui that uses ultralytics to 'fix' faces/hands/body after generation.

Download here - https://github.com/Bing-su/adetailer

Read the information in the Github repo linked above for more info and installation guide.

Neutral Prompt :

Download here - https://github.com/ljleb/sd-webui-neutral-prompt

Note : If you look at gen data for the sample images and see AND_PREP or AND_SALT; then the image used this extension

Neutral Prompt Hack : Okay, it's not really a hack. But I use neutral prompt in a way that it wasn't necessarily designed for.

Let's say you want to really force a specific art style. Open the neutral prompt block in webui and expand the "Format" option. This gives you a CFG slider, prompt box, weight slider, and drop down menu. Leave the dropdown set to "Perpendicular". In the prompt type the artist who's style you're trying to force. For example, by Boris Vallejo. Leave the weight slider at 1 for now, you can change that later if needed. Change the CFG slider (in the extension block) to 0.5. Click the button to append these settings to your prompt.

Your main positive prompt should now end with something like : AND_PREP by Boris Vallejo : 1

Click Generate, it may take a little longer but you should see the art style of the Artist being forced.

This shouldn't really work, and I will need to dig deeper into the math to figure out why it does. I'll update this when I do.

Your results may vary, and for this specific model—it's not really needed. But it's there if you want to give it a try.

Feel free to modify the parameters of the neutral prompt extension, nothing is set in stone.

items.name: Erogen
items.description:
Erogen has been trained on male model photography and amateur shots on top of BOYFUSION to provide a more photoreal/digital art style output compared to BOYFUSION itself for people that were fans of the style of that model prior to the changes around v0.4 and above. This model currently is focused on solo content and will struggle with duos and groups. Can output SFW as well as anime/cel-shading with the right prompts.

Note: This version is a side project based on in-progress versions of BOYFUSION and as such may not receive as frequent of updates as my primary model.

If you feel like supporting further development & caffeine addiction:

  • buymeacoffee.com/atiredhamster

Current Recommended Settings

  • Steps: 26-32

  • Sampler: DPM++ 2M Karras

  • CFG: 7-10

  • Denoising: 0.6-0.7

  • HiRes Steps: 10

  • Upscaler: 4x_NMKD-UltraYandere

Usage Tips

  • Prompts work best when structured as: Composition, Brief Subject Description, Additional Photo Details, Style Details.

  • i.e.: 1boy, Handsome mixed race man sitting on a park bench, sunshine, sunrays, summertime, dutch angle, bokeh

  • Using a short, brief description with no additional details can also provide solid output. i.e. slim fair skin man with long hair sitting on the hood of a car

  • Shorter prompts along with Textual Inversion will provide more stable output.

modelVersions.name: v0.2

v0.2

Rather than build on a slightly broken model, v0.2 has been trained atop an unreleased build of BOYFUSION with more photos of various body types to help add variety and stability to nudes. This version is still solo-focused and as such can likely lead to deformities in duo/group pics.

items.name: John Cazale Lora
items.description:
Greatest actor of all time!

Be nice, have fun!

John Holland Cazale (/kəˈzæl/; August 12, 1935 – March 13, 1978)[2]: 8  was an American actor. He appeared in five films over seven years, all of which were nominated for the Academy Award for Best Picture: The Godfather (1972), The Conversation (1974), The Godfather Part II (1974), Dog Day Afternoon (1975), and The Deer Hunter (1978), with the two Godfather films and The Deer Hunter winning. Cazale started as a theater actor in New York City, ranging from regional, to off-Broadway, to Broadway acting alongside Al Pacino, Meryl Streep, and Sam Waterston. Cazale soon became one of Hollywood's premier character actors, starting with his role as the doomed, weak-minded Fredo Corleone opposite longtime friend Al Pacino in Francis Ford Coppola's film The Godfather and its 1974 sequel, as well as Sidney Lumet's Dog Day Afternoon. In 1977, Cazale was diagnosed with lung cancer, but he chose to complete his role in The Deer Hunter. He died shortly after, in New York City on March 13, 1978.

Theatrical producer Joseph Papp called Cazale "an amazing intellect, an extraordinary person and a fine, dedicated artist".[3] David Thomson writes that "It is the lives and works of people like John Cazale that make filmgoing worthwhile."[4] A documentary tribute to Cazale, I Knew It Was You, was screened at the 2009 Sundance Film Festival featuring interviews with Al Pacino, Steve Buscemi, Meryl Streep, Robert De Niro, Gene Hackman, Richard Dreyfuss, Francis Ford Coppola, and Sidney Lumet.[5]
